Remaining
---------
- i18n
- think about multi-line configuration:
    current_theme = t1, t2, t3
    current_theme = t4, t5
  or
    current_theme = t1, t2, t3 \
		    t4, t5
- FreeBSD fixes

Security audit follow-up
------------------------
- review MidnightBSD-native session accounting and login records
  (PAM, setlogin, and any utmpx/wtmp integration); systemd-logind
  integration is not required for the primary target
- document the security implications of the privileged sessionstart_cmd
  and sessionstop_cmd hooks, or provide a safer execution model
- review the optional screenshot_cmd hook, which runs with login-manager
  privileges when enabled
- review the Linux-specific mlogind.service packaging and provide a
  MidnightBSD-native service definition if needed
